♪From the starting point♪

19
00:01:36,420 --> 00:01:41,380
[South Wind Knows]

20
00:01:41,380 --> 00:01:45,380
[Episode 7]

21
00:01:46,220 --> 00:01:48,220
You sure know how to make the plan
for me.

22
00:01:48,660 --> 00:01:49,540
Come with me, then.

23
00:01:49,660 --> 00:01:50,420
No, thank you.

24
00:01:50,540 --> 00:01:51,540
That's your area of expertise.

25
00:01:51,980 --> 00:01:54,020
My place is in the laboratory.

26
00:01:54,860 --> 00:01:55,540
By the way, Xizhou.

27
00:01:56,100 --> 00:01:57,980
The type of herb I'm looking for
is limited.

28
00:01:58,500 --> 00:02:00,180
When you talk to them later,

29
00:02:00,260 --> 00:02:01,220
can you ask

30
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:04,060
if large-scale cultivation is possible
in the future?

31
00:02:05,860 --> 00:02:07,340
Okay, I'll handle it
as soon as possible.

32
00:02:08,060 --> 00:02:09,780
The company's financial report
for this quarter

33
00:02:09,940 --> 00:02:10,940
doesn't look good.

34
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:12,300
Grandpa and the shareholders are waiting

35
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:14,500
for some good news from us.

36
00:02:15,740 --> 00:02:16,100
Got it.

37
00:02:19,980 --> 00:02:21,020
The photo you took

38
00:02:21,140 --> 00:02:23,100
really captures
their customs and habits.

39
00:02:23,220 --> 00:02:24,380
You did a pretty good job.

40
00:02:25,820 --> 00:02:26,460
Doctor,

41
00:02:26,580 --> 00:02:27,780
please check on the child.

42
00:02:28,060 --> 00:02:28,700
Let me take a look.

43
00:02:28,980 --> 00:02:29,900
Mr. An, what's this?

44
00:02:30,140 --> 00:02:30,780
Mr. An,

45
00:02:31,060 --> 00:02:32,180
please tell this lady

46
00:02:32,260 --> 00:02:33,380
not to worry.

47
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:34,860
This can be treated.

48
00:02:48,860 --> 00:02:49,620
Have some water.

49
00:02:50,340 --> 00:02:52,340
I heard you were shocked today.

50
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:53,860
I wasn't shocked.

51
00:02:54,980 --> 00:02:56,020
Don't worry about it.

52
00:02:56,140 --> 00:02:58,220
That skin condition
is actually quite common.

53
00:03:01,540 --> 00:03:02,940
But he's still so young.

54
00:03:03,020 --> 00:03:05,900
Did you see how it covers his neck?

55
00:03:07,380 --> 00:03:08,860
It does look pretty scary.

56
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:10,580
But this disease

57
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:11,620
mainly affects children.

58
00:03:11,700 --> 00:03:12,900
It's rare in adults.

59
00:03:13,180 --> 00:03:15,740
It usually clears up
in five to seven days with medication.

60
00:03:15,940 --> 00:03:17,180
So don't worry

61
00:03:17,380 --> 00:03:18,500
because it won't leave scars

62
00:03:18,660 --> 00:03:20,100
or any adverse effect

63
00:03:20,220 --> 00:03:21,540
on his future life.

64
00:03:23,060 --> 00:03:24,900
Fortunately, you're all here.

65
00:03:26,940 --> 00:03:27,860
Yeah.

66
00:03:28,260 --> 00:03:29,460
Luckily, we're here.

67
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:31,580
But if those in the more remote areas

68
00:03:31,860 --> 00:03:33,580
don't get proper treatment,

69
00:03:34,180 --> 00:03:35,660
the mortality rate can be quite high.

70
00:03:38,420 --> 00:03:40,300
I can't do anything to help at all.

71
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:41,720
Yet, here I am, being fascinated

72
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:43,340
and taking photos
all over the place every day.

73
00:04:05,580 --> 00:04:06,220
Ruanruan.

74
00:04:06,380 --> 00:04:07,460
To be honest,

75
00:04:07,740 --> 00:04:09,500
I think what you're doing
is very meaningful.

76
00:04:09,780 --> 00:04:11,980
Look, you're taking photos here.

77
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:13,700
When you return,

78
00:04:13,940 --> 00:04:15,980
you can share these photos
with everyone.

79
00:04:16,620 --> 00:04:18,540
Then, when people see these photos,

80
00:04:18,620 --> 00:04:19,900
they will pay attention to this place

81
00:04:20,060 --> 00:04:21,500
and these children.

82
00:04:21,940 --> 00:04:22,780
You're right.

83
00:04:23,980 --> 00:04:25,100
I came here

84
00:04:25,340 --> 00:04:26,740
mainly to investigate

85
00:04:26,820 --> 00:04:28,460
immune system diseases.

86
00:04:28,660 --> 00:04:29,700
Well,

87
00:04:30,660 --> 00:04:31,300
how about this?

88
00:04:31,460 --> 00:04:32,660
Maybe you can take

89
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:34,100
more candid photos
of life here tomorrow.

90
00:04:34,340 --> 00:04:35,060
That's a good idea.

91
00:04:35,180 --> 00:04:36,580
Sure, I'm good at curating.

92
00:04:37,140 --> 00:04:37,820
Later on,

93
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:39,620
I can organize a photography exhibition
for the children.

94
00:04:39,980 --> 00:04:42,100
Maybe we can even raise some funds.

95
00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:43,780
You know what?

96
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:45,460
To me,

97
00:04:45,540 --> 00:04:48,180
even though photographers
can't heal people,

98
00:04:48,540 --> 00:04:51,260
they can inspire many with their photos.

99
00:04:52,020 --> 00:04:52,740
Ruanruan,

100
00:04:53,060 --> 00:04:54,100
I truly think

101
00:04:54,340 --> 00:04:56,460
what you're doing is meaningful.

102
00:04:56,860 --> 00:04:58,540
Thank you for your encouragement.

103
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:00,700
By the way,

104
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:02,140
look at the photos I took today.

105
00:05:03,940 --> 00:05:05,540
You really have talent.

106
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:11,020
Dr. Zhu,

107
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:13,020
thank you
for coming to comfort me today.

108
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:14,740
But I still can't like you

109
00:05:15,140 --> 00:05:16,820
because I'm Zhou Zhizhi's best friend.

110
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:25,060
Professor Hans.

111
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:33,180
Uncle Hans.

112
00:05:34,340 --> 00:05:35,100
How did it go?

113
00:05:37,620 --> 00:05:39,420
There shouldn't be any problems now.

114
00:05:41,140 --> 00:05:41,860
I'm glad to hear that.

115
00:05:42,700 --> 00:05:44,100
I have good news.

116
00:05:44,940 --> 00:05:46,660
The results from both laboratories
are out.

117
00:05:47,060 --> 00:05:49,820
The Perdo extract is indeed effective
against the virus.

118
00:05:49,940 --> 00:05:51,380
Really? That's fantastic.

119
00:05:51,780 --> 00:05:52,940
We need to conduct further research

120
00:05:53,180 --> 00:05:55,140
and synthesize the antiviral medication
as soon as possible.

121
00:05:56,020 --> 00:05:56,700
But

122
00:05:56,820 --> 00:06:00,220
the amount of the herb you've found
is too little.

123
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:01,580
It's not enough

124
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:03,060
for me and Mr. Fu.

125
00:06:04,020 --> 00:06:05,060
Uncle, don't worry.

126
00:06:05,140 --> 00:06:07,300
Yunshen has been with me
during the research.

127
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:09,220
He's very familiar
with the situation here.

128
00:06:09,340 --> 00:06:10,900
He'll definitely prioritize

129
00:06:10,940 --> 00:06:11,860
the children's lives.

130
00:06:12,020 --> 00:06:12,700
Really?

131
00:06:13,980 --> 00:06:14,860
That's great, then.

132
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:15,980
I'll go and talk to him.

133
00:06:16,140 --> 00:06:16,580
All right.

134
00:06:16,900 --> 00:06:17,700
- Thank you for your hard work.
- I'll get going now.

135
00:06:36,580 --> 00:06:37,900
You sure packed up fast.

136
00:06:44,540 --> 00:06:45,500
Why did you want to see me here?

137
00:06:46,580 --> 00:06:47,140
Why?

138
00:06:47,340 --> 00:06:48,660
Can't I reach out to you
unless there's a problem?

139
00:06:48,980 --> 00:06:49,380
Sit down.

140
00:06:50,020 --> 00:06:51,300
Let's warm up by the fire together.

141
00:07:01,660 --> 00:07:04,540
I have good news to share with you.

142
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:07,460
Go on.

143
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:10,420
Uncle Hans said

144
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:12,700
he sent the blood samples
from the sick children

145
00:07:12,820 --> 00:07:15,060
and the Perdo extract to the laboratory.

146
00:07:15,740 --> 00:07:16,860
They got the results today.

147
00:07:18,140 --> 00:07:19,140
We were right.

148
00:07:19,260 --> 00:07:20,420
These children can be saved.

149
00:07:25,660 --> 00:07:26,100
Zhu Jiu,

150
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:29,940
you knew my purpose here, right?

151
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:31,900
Of course, I knew.

152
00:07:31,980 --> 00:07:33,580
That's why I'm here
to ask for your favor.

153
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:35,420
Can you let the professor
have the medicine?

154
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:37,380
You also know how unfortunate
these children are.

155
00:07:45,180 --> 00:07:46,260
I can't make

156
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:49,700
this decision on my own.

157
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:54,060
My brother has been negotiating
with the Chief

158
00:07:54,740 --> 00:07:56,140
for harvesting rights
these past few days.

159
00:07:58,180 --> 00:07:59,180
Harvesting rights?

160
00:07:59,540 --> 00:08:01,700
Are you saying you want
to monopolize these herbs?

161
00:08:04,780 --> 00:08:07,620
I came here specifically for it.

162
00:08:10,020 --> 00:08:10,940
If you take those herbs,

163
00:08:11,020 --> 00:08:12,020
what will happen to the children?

164
00:08:13,260 --> 00:08:14,140
I can apply

165
00:08:14,220 --> 00:08:16,180
for additional medical funds for them
from the company.

166
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:17,140
Funds?

167
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:19,940
Do you think they need money?

168
00:08:20,060 --> 00:08:22,140
They need life-saving medicine!

169
00:08:33,260 --> 00:08:33,940
Zhu Jiu,

170
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:36,500
calm down.

171
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:38,340
Don't confuse things.

172
00:08:39,540 --> 00:08:40,540
In medicine,

173
00:08:41,020 --> 00:08:43,220
finding a research direction
is one thing.

174
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:46,500
Developing medicine to save lives
is another.

175
00:08:47,540 --> 00:08:48,980
Even if I give up the herbs

176
00:08:49,220 --> 00:08:50,580
to Professor Hans,

177
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:51,740
do you know how long it'll take for him

178
00:08:51,820 --> 00:08:52,980
to develop a new medicine?

179
00:08:53,460 --> 00:08:54,820
It could be three or five years.

180
00:08:54,940 --> 00:08:55,940
Or even eight to ten years.

181
00:08:57,020 --> 00:08:57,980
By that time,

182
00:08:58,140 --> 00:08:59,580
- it'll only end...
- What are you trying to say?

183
00:09:01,260 --> 00:09:02,860
These children
will have already died, right?

184
00:09:11,980 --> 00:09:13,340
Don't misinterpret my meaning.

185
00:09:13,540 --> 00:09:15,420
How is every word I say

186
00:09:16,860 --> 00:09:18,940
misinterpreted your words?

187
00:09:24,420 --> 00:09:24,980
Zhu Jiu,

188
00:09:27,460 --> 00:09:29,260
I have my tasks and responsibilities.

189
00:09:30,220 --> 00:09:31,980
The entire company and team are waiting.

190
00:09:32,100 --> 00:09:33,780
Besides, I can use Perdo

191
00:09:34,180 --> 00:09:35,700
to save lives as well.

192
00:09:36,380 --> 00:09:37,020
Yes,

193
00:09:38,180 --> 00:09:39,620
I get that you also develop medicine.

194
00:09:40,340 --> 00:09:41,700
But don't you know

195
00:09:42,620 --> 00:09:45,100
that this might be the only chance
for these children?

196
00:09:46,380 --> 00:09:49,540
In medicine,
there's something called "priority".

197
00:09:59,260 --> 00:10:00,060
Fu Yunshen,

198
00:10:06,460 --> 00:10:07,820
can you help them?

199
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:25,220
I see...

200
00:10:34,620 --> 00:10:35,260
Zhu Jiu.

201
00:10:38,340 --> 00:10:39,340
Can you try to put yourself

202
00:10:41,420 --> 00:10:42,660
in my shoes?

203
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:48,620
I can.

204
00:10:51,260 --> 00:10:52,940
I can understand
where you're coming from.

205
00:10:54,580 --> 00:10:56,660
But asking me to give up everything?

206
00:10:58,540 --> 00:11:00,020
I really can't do it.

207
00:11:02,380 --> 00:11:04,860
I can't pretend I never came here,

208
00:11:07,020 --> 00:11:08,540
never did the research.

209
00:11:15,260 --> 00:11:16,700
Pretend not to know

210
00:11:18,260 --> 00:11:19,460
these children

211
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:22,020
might still have a chance to live.

212
00:11:28,580 --> 00:11:29,900
I really can't do it.

